   "source": [
    "### Conduct PCA and visualize variance explained by principal components\n",
    "**Principal Component Analysis (PCA)** is a dimensionality reduction technique that compresses large datasets into a much smaller set of features while minimizing information loss. It is done by taking the eigenvalues and eigevectors of the covariance matrix . The eigenvectors determine the linear transformations that create the principal components (by maximizing variance capture) while the eigenvalues determine how much variance is captured along that principal component. "
   ]
  },
